    {
      "id": "be4f407dabf0618b49306dc87824020f90a0bb2f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-18 07:58:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThis is good, but my understanding is that open_bdev_exclusive() is the old API and blkdev_get_by_path(..., O_EXCL) is the new API?  It would be better to use the new API in the code, so that the compat macros and configure checks can eventually be deleted without further changes to the code.\n\nThat said, it does appear that wrapping blkdev_get_by_path() inside open_bdev_exclusive() is easier to implement properly, so if the reverse isn't possible to do then I'm ok to keep the current patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "f7f7571aafdfef59e75f54b5b6deff098f8792f1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-29 13:50:00.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nAbandoned in favor of Gerrit change #11139 with :\nChange-Id: I442819a5b865ed3e98477f9d2602efc4d09d7860\nCommit: cddb0893d52183d8c02a63bbf0239ab489b2f8eb\n\nsince it is not possible to implement multiple/concurrent mount protection this way because same device is mounted twice (lustre+backend) in same context.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    }
