          "date": "2014-07-17 14:57:59.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-5299 obdclass: avoid race during Server device mount",
        "message": "LU-5299 obdclass: avoid race during Server device mount\n\nEnsure bdev is opened exclusive to ensure atomicity of all\noperations during mount process and avoid any side effects\nduring potential race (dual mount, ...).\n\nBut 2.6.38 Kernel introduced some API changes, and\nopen_bdev_exclusive()/close_bdev_exclusive() need to be replaced\nby blkdev_get_by_path()/blkdev_put() calls with explicit setting\nof FMODE_EXCL mode.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5904553175dd3fdf6fe68b5318ebba2f4b605563\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
